        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 12:46AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1245 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Mayflower, or 14 miles west of Toledo Bend Dam,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hemphill, Fairmount, and Yellowpine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
